Oh? Do tell.

249
00:11:48,666 --> 00:11:50,416
Like my new bonnet?

250
00:11:50,500 --> 00:11:51,791
[EMA chuckles]

251
00:11:54,541 --> 00:11:57,333
[SOLDIERS yelp]

252
00:11:57,416 --> 00:11:58,666
You have my thanks!

253
00:11:58,750 --> 00:11:59,916
Yeah?

254
00:12:00,000 --> 00:12:01,333
But it seemed like you
were having such fun.

255
00:12:01,416 --> 00:12:05,833
Your definition of fun is
a very broad one, indeed.

256
00:12:15,750 --> 00:12:17,125
My word.

257
00:12:17,208 --> 00:12:20,875
Your son almost dies last
night and I find you naked.

258
00:12:20,958 --> 00:12:23,083
Oh? What happened to him?

259
00:12:23,166 --> 00:12:24,791
He fought the Black Knight.

260
00:12:24,875 --> 00:12:27,000
León was no match
for one such as him.

261
00:12:27,083 --> 00:12:28,875
The Black Knight?

262
00:12:28,958 --> 00:12:32,583
Yes. His name is Bernardo Dion.

263
00:12:32,666 --> 00:12:34,750
[gasps]

264
00:12:34,833 --> 00:12:36,500
I take it you know him?

265
00:12:36,583 --> 00:12:37,875
Where's León?

266
00:12:37,958 --> 00:12:40,750
He managed to escape,
although not by much.

267
00:12:40,833 --> 00:12:43,500
I'd have followed,
but the guard was after me.

268
00:12:43,583 --> 00:12:45,625
[sighs]

269
00:12:45,708 --> 00:12:48,541
What, not rushing to his side?

270
00:12:48,625 --> 00:12:51,583
It's enough that León is alive.

271
00:12:51,666 --> 00:12:53,958
I only hope that he
can take this defeat

272
00:12:54,041 --> 00:12:58,041
as something to learn from.
The day draws near.

273
00:12:58,125 --> 00:13:02,916
I pray my son will discover
what he lacks in time.

274
00:13:03,000 --> 00:13:05,500
It is the sworn duty
of you Makai Knights

275
00:13:05,583 --> 00:13:07,125
to defend and protect.

276
00:13:07,208 --> 00:13:08,875
If the boy only
seeks to gain power

277
00:13:08,958 --> 00:13:12,041
out of his desire for revenge...

278
00:13:12,125 --> 00:13:15,375
He may never be worthy
of the Golden Armor.

279
00:13:20,500 --> 00:13:24,208
[GERMÁN] Thanks for the
rescue. As for him...

280
00:13:24,291 --> 00:13:26,666
I'll do what needs to be done.

281
00:13:29,750 --> 00:13:32,375
You finding pants
is what needs doing.

282
00:13:32,458 --> 00:13:33,500
[GERMÁN]
Quite.

283
00:13:54,666 --> 00:13:56,416
Hello there.

284
00:13:59,583 --> 00:14:01,166
[GERMÁN exhales]

285
00:14:01,250 --> 00:14:03,291
[GARM]
Hm?

286
00:14:04,666 --> 00:14:07,458
[GARM, GERMÁN]
What's the meaning of this?

287
00:14:07,541 --> 00:14:10,916
U-Uh-- Ahem.
Bernardo still lives,

288
00:14:11,000 --> 00:14:12,500
and yet you said nothing.

289
00:14:12,583 --> 00:14:15,000
It wouldn't change your
hunt for Mendooza,

290
00:14:15,083 --> 00:14:16,458
now would it?

291
00:14:16,541 --> 00:14:19,208
I simply neglected to tell
you he was likely to appear.

292
00:14:19,291 --> 00:14:21,500
It seemed rather
irrelevant information.

293
00:14:21,583 --> 00:14:25,666
It's about time I tell you this.
You can sometimes annoy.

294
00:14:25,750 --> 00:14:29,333
[GARM] You wound me,
sweet Zoro. Don't you see?

295
00:14:29,416 --> 00:14:31,958
I kept silent to keep
your pretty mortal heart

296
00:14:32,041 --> 00:14:35,875
from quivering and breaking
at the very thought.

297
00:14:35,958 --> 00:14:39,250
The truth. Is he fallen?

298
00:14:39,333 --> 00:14:42,250
He yet lives, drowned
in the shadows.

299
00:14:42,333 --> 00:14:44,541
I do weep for his loss.

300
00:14:44,625 --> 00:14:48,083
Tch. We are but dogs
for your purpose.

301
00:14:53,000 --> 00:14:54,833
Come, Anna! Keep up with us!

302
00:14:54,916 --> 00:14:56,625
You can shout back
at me all you want,

303
00:14:56,708 --> 00:14:59,458
but it doesn't mean the horse
will suddenly do what I say!

304
00:14:59,541 --> 00:15:00,875
Too bad about Anna.

305
00:15:00,958 --> 00:15:03,833
Her hands spur neither
horses nor men to action.

306
00:15:03,916 --> 00:15:05,333
That's quite uncouth.

307
00:15:05,416 --> 00:15:06,500
No, this is uncouth.

308
00:15:06,583 --> 00:15:08,625
If you catch me, Anna,
you can have me!

309
00:15:08,708 --> 00:15:10,208
God, you're such a letch.

310
00:15:10,291 --> 00:15:13,500
Hyah! Ah! No, wait!

311
00:15:13,583 --> 00:15:14,708
Woah!

312
00:15:14,791 --> 00:15:16,000
[gasps]

313
00:15:21,041 --> 00:15:23,583
Ow. Ow, ow, ow.

314
00:15:23,666 --> 00:15:24,791
Are you all right, Anna?

315
00:15:24,875 --> 00:15:27,625
Uh, yes. Think so.

316
00:15:27,708 --> 00:15:29,333
[GERMÁN]
Truly an astounding dismount.

317
00:15:29,416 --> 00:15:30,916
Thank God you're unharmed.

318
00:15:31,000 --> 00:15:33,333
Or perhaps you just owe it all
to your "natural cushioning"?

319
00:15:33,416 --> 00:15:35,291
[ANNA] Your cushioning's
all in your skull.

320
00:15:35,375 --> 00:15:36,500
[GERMÁN]
Here. Hop up.

321
00:15:36,583 --> 00:15:38,000
[ANNA]
Fine.

322
00:15:40,708 --> 00:15:41,916
Thank you.

323
00:15:42,000 --> 00:15:52,833
[GERMÁN, BERNARDO grunting]

324
00:15:52,916 --> 00:15:53,916
One of these days,

325
00:15:54,000 --> 00:15:55,708
I'd like to take you on
in a true fight!

326
00:15:55,791 --> 00:15:57,125
Just say the word, then.

327
00:15:57,208 --> 00:16:01,250
You know that we can't!
Our code forbids us such duels.

328
00:16:01,333 --> 00:16:03,958
You never were one to
break the rules, were ya?

329
00:16:04,041 --> 00:16:06,875
[BERNARDO]
Hm? I wish that I could.

330
00:16:06,958 --> 00:16:07,875
Huh?

331
00:16:09,000 --> 00:16:10,666
Many's the time my
soul has cried out

332
00:16:10,750 --> 00:16:13,291
for me to spurn
our oath altogether.

333
00:16:13,375 --> 00:16:15,333
In a voice loud as thunder.

334
00:16:15,416 --> 00:16:16,375
Truly?

335
00:16:16,458 --> 00:16:17,458
[BERNARDO grunts]

336
00:16:20,750 --> 00:16:23,416
Well! That was creative.

337
00:16:23,500 --> 00:16:27,416
[BERNARDO] Hmph. That was
a victory, friend.

338
00:16:27,500 --> 00:16:29,208
[GERMÁN]
Victory? Anna!

339
00:16:29,291 --> 00:16:31,833
Can you believe this cheater?
He's still counting it!

340
00:16:31,916 --> 00:16:33,541
Better keep your eye on him!

341
00:16:33,625 --> 00:16:34,916
[ANNA giggles]

342
00:16:38,583 --> 00:16:40,041
[SOLDIER 8L] The witch!
They're fleeing with her!

343
00:16:40,125 --> 00:16:41,000
[SOLDIER 8K]
After them! Quick!

344
00:16:41,083 --> 00:16:42,250
[SOLDIER 8M]
Hurry, men!

345
00:16:45,458 --> 00:16:47,833
[GERMÁN grunts, groans]

346
00:16:47,916 --> 00:16:49,291
Roberto!

347
00:16:51,625 --> 00:16:53,916
[GERMÁN]
Anna! Are you all right?

348
00:16:54,000 --> 00:16:56,666
[ANNA]
Ah. Yes. We are.

349
00:16:56,750 --> 00:16:57,666
[gasps]

350
00:16:57,750 --> 00:17:00,666
[BERNARDO]
Roberto! We must fly!

351
00:17:00,750 --> 00:17:02,791
You're right. Let's go, then.

352
00:17:02,875 --> 00:17:04,916
[gasps]

353
00:17:05,000 --> 00:17:08,416
[GERMÁN] Just a nick.
Here, you should take Anna.

354
00:17:08,500 --> 00:17:10,666
Quickly, now. Both of
you mount up.

355
00:17:10,750 --> 00:17:12,541
I can lead them down
another street.

356
00:17:12,625 --> 00:17:13,750
[GERMÁN]
Are you an idiot?

357
00:17:13,833 --> 00:17:14,958
You know that I'm
the better swords--

358
00:17:15,041 --> 00:17:16,291
Listen to me!

359
00:17:16,375 --> 00:17:19,416
You haven't much chance
with one arm running red!

360
00:17:19,500 --> 00:17:20,750
What're you gonna do?

361
00:17:20,833 --> 00:17:23,458
You damn well can't fight
them all on your own.

362
00:17:23,541 --> 00:17:24,750
I'll find a way.

363
00:17:24,833 --> 00:17:27,375
This, is our only
option, my friend.

364
00:17:27,458 --> 00:17:29,708
[GERMÁN grunts]

365
00:17:29,791 --> 00:17:31,125
You think you can ride?

366
00:17:31,208 --> 00:17:32,666
I think so.

367
00:17:32,750 --> 00:17:37,583
[hooves clacking]

368
00:17:37,666 --> 00:17:38,833
Now go!

369
00:17:38,916 --> 00:17:39,583
Fight well.

370
00:17:39,666 --> 00:17:41,333
We will find you!

371
00:17:43,250 --> 00:17:44,291
Ride hard.

372
00:17:44,375 --> 00:17:46,458
Thank me when next we meet.

373
00:17:46,541 --> 00:17:49,541
[SOLDIERS yelling]

374
00:17:56,208 --> 00:18:06,083
[BERNARDO groaning]

375
00:18:06,583 --> 00:18:07,833
[BERNARDO yells]

376
00:18:07,916 --> 00:18:14,541
[BERNARDO groans]

377
00:18:14,625 --> 00:18:18,166
[BERNARDO]
Forgive me, Roberto.

378
00:18:18,250 --> 00:18:21,916
As of tonight, I wear the
armor of righteousness,

379
00:18:22,000 --> 00:18:23,541
no longer.

380
00:18:34,333 --> 00:18:37,375
[BERNARDO]
Face me, Roberto.

381
00:18:39,041 --> 00:18:42,000
[GERMÁN sneezes]

382
00:18:42,083 --> 00:18:46,333
Bernardo's alive. He'll come.

383
00:18:46,416 --> 00:18:49,333
And I can do naught
but brace myself.

384
00:18:57,458 --> 00:18:58,416
Just my luck.

385
00:18:58,500 --> 00:19:00,791
My clothes are
nowhere to be found.

386
00:19:00,875 --> 00:19:02,625
It's that kinda day.

387
00:19:03,833 --> 00:19:05,291
[GERMÁN grunts]

388
00:19:06,833 --> 00:19:07,875
Oh, now what?

389
00:19:07,958 --> 00:19:09,875
[gasps] Not you again!

390
00:19:09,958 --> 00:19:13,375
Good sir. Thank
heavens it's you!

391
00:19:13,458 --> 00:19:16,291
Huh? You can spare me the tears.

392
00:19:16,375 --> 00:19:19,166
I have nothing else you
can steal. You took it all!

393
00:19:19,250 --> 00:19:21,791
Look, twice in one day
seems a little ambitious.

394
00:19:21,875 --> 00:19:25,791
How about you go ply
your con elsewhere.

395
00:19:25,875 --> 00:19:29,791
[IRENE sobs]

396
00:19:29,875 --> 00:19:31,166
Tell me what happened.

397
00:19:31,250 --> 00:19:34,541
I can't even be sure.

398
00:19:34,625 --> 00:19:35,750
But, well,

399
00:19:35,833 --> 00:19:37,916
after you ran away,
Donato got really angry,

400
00:19:38,000 --> 00:19:40,708
worse than I'd ever seen before!

401
00:19:40,791 --> 00:19:44,666
He attacked us! Please,
please, believe me!

402
00:19:44,750 --> 00:19:47,416
Easy. I know it's true.

403
00:19:50,083 --> 00:19:53,041
[DONATO growling]

404
00:19:53,125 --> 00:19:55,291
[gasps] No. It's Donato!

405
00:19:55,375 --> 00:19:57,500
It'll be all right. Now, Irene.

406
00:19:57,583 --> 00:19:59,583
Please tell me where
I can find my clothes.

407
00:19:59,666 --> 00:20:01,291
Um. A pawn shop.

408
00:20:01,375 --> 00:20:02,416
Aw, dammit!

409
00:20:02,500 --> 00:20:04,583
[DONATO grunts]

410
00:20:08,500 --> 00:20:10,083
[gasps, screams]

411
00:20:10,166 --> 00:20:13,833
No time. Naked it is, then.

412
00:20:13,916 --> 00:20:16,083
[HORROR DONATO growls]

413
00:20:16,166 --> 00:20:19,583
Hey, wait! Stop!
I'm not ready! Not ready!

414
00:20:19,666 --> 00:20:21,416
[HORROR DONATO growls]

415
00:20:21,500 --> 00:20:22,750
[GERMÁN grunts]

416
00:20:25,166 --> 00:20:26,750
You bastard!

417
00:20:27,791 --> 00:20:30,833
I will not lose
in front of a lady!

418
00:20:30,916 --> 00:20:36,125
[HORROR DONATO groans]

419
00:20:38,166 --> 00:20:43,083
[IRENE whimpering]

420
00:20:44,250 --> 00:20:46,916
[GERMÁN] Continue down
this path, and you, too,

421
00:20:47,000 --> 00:20:48,250
will become a monster.

422
00:20:48,333 --> 00:20:51,583
[IRENE whimpers]

423
00:20:55,250 --> 00:20:56,458
Don't you fret.

424
00:20:56,541 --> 00:20:58,625
If you like, I can
stay and keep watch.

425
00:20:58,708 --> 00:21:00,541
You'll be safe with me.

426
00:21:03,000 --> 00:21:05,458
But, I can be
pretty intimidating.

427
00:21:05,541 --> 00:21:07,458
Scarier than any monster.

428
00:21:07,541 --> 00:21:09,625
[IRENE chuckles]

429
00:21:09,708 --> 00:21:14,750
[wolf howls]

430
00:21:15,875 --> 00:21:19,375
[GERMÁN yawns]

431
00:21:20,916 --> 00:21:23,416
[SOLDIER 8N] There he is!
The degenerate's still naked!

432
00:21:23,500 --> 00:21:28,333
You're kidding! Leave me alone!

433
00:21:28,416 --> 00:21:29,083
[XIMENA humming]

434
00:21:29,166 --> 00:21:31,500
[GERMÁN panting]

435
00:21:31,583 --> 00:21:33,125
[SOLDIER 8O]
Halt, man!

436
00:21:34,666 --> 00:21:36,625
[giggles]

437
00:21:44,208 --> 00:21:47,375
[GERMÁN]
León. Good to see you.

438
00:21:47,458 --> 00:21:49,000
Is it really?

439
00:21:49,083 --> 00:21:51,708
Ema told me what happened
during the fight.

440
00:21:51,791 --> 00:21:54,125
That you lost to the
man in the dark armor.

441
00:21:54,208 --> 00:21:56,250
[LEÓN grunts]

442
00:21:56,333 --> 00:21:58,708
It's time to rise
to the challenge.

443
00:21:58,791 --> 00:22:01,291
I can't help you until you do.

444
00:22:01,375 --> 00:22:02,958
I know, thanks.

445
00:22:03,041 --> 00:22:05,333
[GERMÁN]
So what's the plan?

446
00:22:05,416 --> 00:22:08,291
I guess I could use some time.

447
00:22:08,375 --> 00:22:10,416
[GERMÁN]
León, wait.

448
00:22:11,625 --> 00:22:13,875
[GERMÁN] I don't wanna
bore you with details.

449
00:22:13,958 --> 00:22:17,000
Suffice it to say,
I'm naked, and I'm broke.

450
00:22:17,083 --> 00:22:19,208
I'm in a bit of a pickle.

451
00:22:20,500 --> 00:22:22,208
[LEÓN sighs]

452
00:22:22,291 --> 00:22:23,916
[GERMÁN groans]

453
00:22:25,958 --> 00:22:29,291
[GERMÁN]
I'll be waiting, my son.

454
00:24:03,541 --> 00:24:06,041
[GARM]
Hope, it seems, is inherited.

455
00:24:06,125 --> 00:24:08,458
And the lessons instilled
in one's heart.

456
00:24:08,541 --> 00:24:11,375
so fast are sworn into vows.

